Description: The Kith x ASICS Gel 1130 ‘Cream Starlight Blue’ is taken from a collaborative four-piece footwear collection. The lifestyle runner carries an airy white mesh upper with durable synthetic leather overlays in a metallic silver finish. Side stripes in bright teal provide pastel pops of color. The lightweight build rests on a high-rebound SpEVA midsole, fitted with visible ASICS Gel cushioning in the heel. Underfoot, a durable black rubber outsole provides grippy traction.

Name: ASICS Gel-Kayano 14 Kith Cream Scarab
Description: Dropping as part of a collaborative four-piece pack, the Kith x ASICS Gel Kayano 14 ‘Cream Scarab’ brings a refined palette to the lifestyle runner. Showcasing a late 2000s aesthetic, the upper blends airy off-white mesh with shiny synthetic leather overlays in metallic silver. Contrasting hits of color arrive via signature side stripes in a dark green hue. A vintage finish is applied to the lightweight EVA midsole, featuring visible Gel cushioning in the heel for a comfortable ride.

Name: ASICS Gel-Kayano 14 Kith Cream Antler
Description: Launching as part of a four-piece footwear collection, the Kith x ASICS Gel Kayano 14 ‘Cream Antler’ delivers a subtle colorway of the retro running shoe. Ventilated off-white mesh is utilized on the upper, contrasted by metallic silver synthetic leather overlays and signature side stripes in a dull mauve hue. ASICS branding appears on the tongue, while ‘Gel Kayano 14’ is inscribed on the lateral heel. The sneaker rides on a full-length EVA midsole with visible Gel cushioning in the heel.

Name: ASICS Gel-1130 Kith Cream Scarab
Description: Drawn from a four-piece footwear collection, the Kith x ASICS Gel 1130 ‘Cream Scarab’ showcases a lightweight, summer-ready build with high-rebound cushioning. The lifestyle running shoe makes use of a breathable off-white mesh upper, contrasted by dark green side stripes and synthetic leather overlays in metallic silver. Underpinning the sneaker is a responsive SpEVA midsole, fitted with visible Gel cushioning in the heel and ASICS’ TRUSSTIC support system under the midfoot.

Description: Dropping as part of the brand’s Valentine’s Day collection, the Converse Chuck Taylor All Star High GS ‘White’ carries a traditional canvas upper festooned with unique details in honor of February 14. They include heart-printed laces, an embroidered heart on the lateral side and a ‘Made With Love’ graphic on the opposite side. Underfoot, the white rubber outsole features a traditional diamond traction pattern and an all-over print made up of additional red hearts.

Yeezy Boost 700 'Utility Black' 2023
Description: The 2023 reissue of the adidas Yeezy Boost 700 ‘Utility Black’ brings back a stealthy colorway originally released in 2019. The retro-inspired model carries a ventilated black mesh upper with tonal overlays in leather and suede. Reflective accents, including hidden three-stripes beneath the mesh quarter panel, offer improved visibility in low-light conditions. Lightweight cushioning is provided by a drop-in Boost midsole, housed within a sculpted PU carrier for added durability. Underfoot, a gum rubber outsole features a herringbone traction pattern for superior grip.

Name: adidas Stan Smith The Simpsons Homer Simpson
Description: The Simpsons x adidas Stan Smith ‘Homer Simpson’ pays tribute to the iconic animated TV dad. The character’s name is stamped in gold-foil lettering on the white leather upper, while his likeness appears on the printed Stan Smith tag that adorns the tongue. The shoe’s standout feature takes the form of the heel tab, which depicts a snapshot of an instantly recognizable GIF — that of a wide-eyed Homer Simpson walking backward into lush green hedges. Underpinning the sneaker is a durable rubber cupsole in an antique cream-colored finish.

Name: adidas Yeezy Slide Slate Grey
Description: The adidas Yeezy Slide ‘Slate Grey’ presents a neutral colorway of the lightweight and durable slip-on silhouette. A medium grey finish is applied to the one-piece build, composed of injected EVA foam with a seamless wide-strap upper. Exterior branding is limited to adidas’ three-stripe logo debossed on the footbed, featuring a soft top layer for step-in comfort. Underfoot, deep grooves in the outsole provide superior traction and a comfortable ride.

Name: Yeezy Boost 700 'Wave Runner' 2023
Description: The 2023 edition of the Yeezy Boost 700 brings back the original 'Wave Runner' colorway, first released in 2017. The upper utilizes mixed materials, including leather, mesh, suede and 3M, while the sculpted midsole houses Boost for lightweight cushioning. The shoe is mostly grey and black, save for a splash of blue and teal on the forefoot, two orange hits on the midsole and yellow laces.

Name: adidas Yeezy Slide Slate Marine
Description: The adidas Yeezy Slide ‘Slate Marine’ pairs a minimalist design with a tonal finish in a subdued shade of blue. Built with a single piece of injected EVA foam, the slip-on boasts a wide strap upper that entirely covers the top of the foot. Exterior branding is limited to adidas’ three stripes logo, debossed on the soft top lay of the footbed. Underfoot, the outsole features a series of horizontal grooves for improved cushioning and traction.

Name: adidas Yeezy Foam RNR Carbon
Description: The adidas Yeezy Foam Runner ‘Carbon’ brings a stealthy one-note finish to the futuristic slip-on. A dark shade of grey is applied to the one-piece build, made with injected EVA foam and featuring flowing lines and a sculpted heel designed to cradle the back of the foot. Strategically mapped vents throughout the vamp and side panels provide enhanced breathability, while the textured footbed offers a comfortable fit. Underpinning the clog-like silhouette is a durable rubber outsole.

Name: Bad Bunny x Campus 'Chalky Brown'
Description: Continuing a creative partnership that began in 2021, the Bad Bunny x adidas Campus ‘Chalky Brown’ delivers the chart-topping recording artist’s distinctive take on the iconic silhouette. The low-top makes use of a brown hairy suede upper, accented with tonal three-stripe branding and equipped with double-tongue construction. Inspired by ocean waves, an evolved rubber mudguard in a cream-colored finish gives way to a durable rubber cupsole, featuring a herringbone traction pattern underfoot.

Name: adidas Response CL Bad Bunny Triple Black
Description: The Bad Bunny x adidas Response CL ‘Triple Black’ reunites the creative partners on a stealthy colorway of the lifestyle runner. The upper is composed of breathable black mesh, accented with navy TPU three-stripes and bolstered with tonal wavy overlays in durable synthetic leather. Tonal adidas branding appears on the tongue, while Bad Bunny’s third eye graphic decorates the heel tab. The sneaker rides on a full-length EVA midsole in a matching black finish.

Name: adidas NMD S1 Bliss
BAPE x Forum Low 84 '30th Anniversary - Blue'
Description: Celebrating the influential streetwear brand’s 30th anniversary, the BAPE x adidas Forum Low 84 ‘’Blue’ updates the heritage hoops shoe with a street-ready aesthetic. BAPE’s ABC Camo print in varying shades of blue is applied to the leather upper, contrasted by white paneling on the toe box and midfoot. The latter is accented with navy three-stripes, while metallic silver 30th anniversary branding decorates the tongue tag and lace dubrae. Anchoring the sneaker is a durable cupsole, highlighted by aged sidewalls and a navy rubber outsole.

Jordan 14 Retro Black White
Description: The Air Jordan 14 Retro ‘Black White’ arrives in an essential two-tone colorway. Crafted from black suede, the upper features an asymmetrical collar and stitched lines throughout the side panel. On the lateral side, a Jumpman badge takes inspiration from Ferrari’s prancing horse emblem. White accents stand out on the black Phylon midsole, enhanced with encapsulated Zoom Air cushioning in the forefoot and heel. A herringbone-pattern rubber outsole delivers grippy traction underfoot.

Name: Jordan 8 Retro Winterized Gunsmoke (GS)
Jordan 1 Mid SS Six Championships (GS)
Jordan 3 Retro Fear Pack (2023) (GS)
Description: Offered in grade school sizing, the 2023 edition of the Air Jordan 3 Retro GS ‘Fear’ revives a sleek colorway originally released in 2013. The upper is crafted from dark grey nubuck with tonal elephant print overlays at the forefoot and heel. Total Orange accents land on the shoe’s eyelets, along with Jumpman branding hits at the tongue and molded heel tab. The mid-top rides on an Air-assisted foam midsole, featuring a crisp white finish with a contrasting topline in a gradient blend of grey and black.

Name: Jordan 5 Retro A Ma Maniére Dusk
Description: The A Ma Maniére x Air Jordan 5 Retro ‘Dusk’ reunites the creative partners on a two sneaker collaborative pack. This pair carries a black nubuck upper, updated with a slimmed-down collar and pre-yellowed quarter panel netting formed with an interlocking series of A Ma Maniére’s signature ‘A’ logo. ‘Nike Air’ branding is embroidered on the back heel in tonal fashion, while silver reflective tongues display mismatched Jumpman and A Ma Maniére branding. The sneaker sits atop a matching black polyurethane midsole with shark-tooth detailing in a dark burgundy hue. A pre-aged translucent rubber outsole featuring the Atlanta-based retailer’s logo provides durable traction underfoot.

Name: Jordan 13 Retro Wheat (2023) (GS)
Description: Made for big kids, the 2023 edition of the Air Jordan 13 Retro GS ‘Wheat’ brings back a two-tone colorway originally released in 2004. The upper features white leather construction on the shoe’s dimpled overlays and toe, along with beige suede paneling that extends from the midfoot and around the heel. A green-tinted holograph ‘eye’ adorns the lateral collar, while an embroidered Jumpman graces the tongue. Lightweight cushioning arrives via a white Phylon midsole, partially wrapped in beige synthetic suede and supported by a panther-paw rubber outsole.

Name: Jordan 4 Retro SE Craft Medium Olive (GS)
Description: Made for big kids, the Air Jordan 4 Retro SE GS Craft in ‘Olive’ features a layered upper in nubuck and suede. Quarter panels are updated with embossed suede in a gridded pattern, replacing the TPU netting of the original. Contrasting black accents settle on the shoe’s leather support wings, molded eyelets and textile collar lining. A cream-colored Jumpman logo adorns the woven tongue tag and semi-translucent back tab. Undergirding the sneaker is a lightweight foam midsole with visible Air-sole cushioning.

Name: Jordan 4 Retro SE Craft Medium Olive (PS)
Description: Built for little kids, the Air Jordan 4 Retro SE GS Craft in ‘Olive’ makes use of a layered upper in a tonal blend of nubuck and suede. The quarter panel discards the TPU netting of the original in favor of embossed suede in a gridded pattern. Black textile lines the collar, matching the eyelets and leather support wings. A cream-hued Jumpman logo adorns the tongue and semi-translucent back tab. The mid-top rests on a white foam midsole, supported by a herringbone-traction rubber outsole.

Name: Jordan 2 Retro Origins
Description: The Air Jordan 2 Retro ‘Origins’ showcases a distinctive color scheme that nods to the shoe’s premium roots. (The original 1986 release paired an elegant Swooshless design with made-in-Italy construction.) This pair dons a white leather upper with faux lizard skin on the midfoot overlay. The latter is outlined in two-tone piping in red and green, with the contrasting hues making a repeat appearance on the Nike-branded heel tab. Crimson textile lines the high-cut collar, matching the embossed Wings logo that decorates the tongue. A vintage off-white finish is applied to the polyurethane midsole, fitted with encapsulated Air-sole cushioning and supported by a two-tone rubber outsole.

Name: Jordan 2 Retro Origins (GS)
Description: Made for big kids, the Air Jordan 2 Retro GS ‘Origins’ gets dressed in a color scheme that references the silhouette’s continental provenance. (The original 1986 launch paired premium materials with made-in-Italy craftsmanship.) Built with smooth white leather, the upper retains the lizard-textured overlay of the OG AJ2. The midfoot panel is surrounded by red and green piping, with the contrasting hues making repeat appearances on the shoe’s heel and interior lining. Branding elements include a Nike wordmark on the back tab and an embossed Wings logo on the tongue. Anchoring the sneaker is an off-white foam midsole with encapsulated Air-sole cushioning.

Name: Jordan 2 Retro Origins (PS)
Description: Made for little kids, the Air Jordan 2 Retro PS ‘Origins’ features accent colors inspired by the shoe’s premium ‘80s roots. The legacy silhouette makes use of a white leather upper with a lizard-textured midfoot overlay outlined in red and green piping. Exterior branding elements are limited to an embossed Wings logo on the tongue and a Nike wordmark on the heel tab, both of which are rendered in a bold Fire Red finish. A contrasting hit of Fir Green lands on the heel counter. Anchoring the sneaker is a vintage off-white midsole built with cushy foam.

Name: Jordan 11 Retro DMP Gratitude (2023) (GS)
Description: Crafted for big kids, he Air Jordan 11 Retro GS ‘Gratitude / Defining Moments’ features color blocking reminiscent of the iconic ‘Concord’ AJ11, highlighted by a white leather upper with tonal webbing eyelets and a contrasting black mudguard in glossy patent leather. A metallic gold Jumpman shines on the lateral collar, matching the stylized ‘23’ stamped on the back tab. The sneaker rests on a cushy white Phylon midsole, supported underfoot by a cream-tinted semi-translucent rubber outsole.

Name: Jordan 11 Retro DMP Gratitude (2023)
Description: The 2023 edition of the Air Jordan 11 Retro 'Gratitude / Defining Moments', also known as 'DMP', brings back a coveted colorway of the legacy model, originally paired with an Air Jordan 6 as one-half of the 'Defining Moments Pack' from 2006. Inspired by the OG 'Concord' colorway, the championship silhouette features a white tumbled leather upper with tonal webbing eyelets and a black patent leather mudguard. Metallic gold accents land on the shoe's branding elements, including an embossed Jumpman logo on the lateral ankle and a '23' stamped on the heel tab. The sneaker rides on a Phylon midsole, supported by a carbon fiber shank plate and a translucent rubber outsole.

Name: Jordan 5 Retro Georgetown
Description: The Air Jordan 5 Retro SE ‘Midnight Navy’ highlights a tonal finish on the textile and suede upper, equipped with a padded collar and breathable quarter panel netting. Molded black eyelets match the Jumpman logos that decorate the tongue and back heel. The sneaker sits atop a white polyurethane midsole with speckled shark-tooth detailing and a visible Air-sole unit in the heel. A blue-tinted translucent rubber outsole featuring herringbone traction pattern for optimal grip completes the look.

Name: Jordan 5 Retro Georgetown (GS)
Description: Built for big kids, the Air Jordan 5 Retro SE GS ‘Midnight Navy’ utilizes textile paneling on the midfoot and toe box, while tonal suede construction appears throughout the padded collar and heel overlay. The latter is accented with an embroidered black Jumpman, matching a second Jumpman logo on the tongue. A contrasting white foam midsole features speckled shark tooth detailing and a visible Air-sole unit in the heel. Underfoot, a translucent rubber outsole yields durable traction.

Name: Jordan Luka 2 The Pitch
Colorway: Laser Orange/Hyper Jade/Black/Light Orewood Brown/Gum Light Brown

Name: Jordan Luka 2 The Pitch (GS)
Colorway: Laser Orange/Hyper Jade/Black/Light Orewood Brown/Gum Light Brown

Name: Jordan 1 Retro High OG Royal Reimagined
Description: The Air Jordan 1 Retro High OG ‘Royal Reimagined’ brings back the original 1985 colorway utilizing different materials. Replacing the leather construction of the original, the upper is draped in smooth suede, featuring a black base with contrasting royal blue accents on the toe box, Swoosh, heel and collar overlay. The latter is marked with the iconic Jordan Wings logo, while a woven Nike Air tag adorns the breathable nylon tongue. The classic silhouette is mounted on a sturdy rubber cupsole, highlighted by white sidewalls and a grippy royal blue outsole.

Name: Jordan 12 Retro Cherry (2023)
Description: The 2023 edition of the Air Jordan 12 Retro ‘Cherry’ reintroduces the OG colorway of the shoe that Michael Jordan wore during his penultimate championship season. Highlighted with radiating stitched lines, the white leather upper is fortified with lizard-textured overlays in a bold scarlet finish. The Jumpman logo graces the tongue in black embroidery, matching the shoe’s textile collar lining. The sneaker rides on a Phylon midsole with full-length Zoom Air cushioning. Underfoot, the semi-translucent red rubber outsole reveals black herringbone traction pods and an exposed carbon fiber shank plate.

Name: Jordan 1 Retro Low OG Chris Paul
Description: The Chris Paul x Air Jordan 1 Retro Low OG ‘Give Them Flowers’ features a debossed tonal floral pattern on the white leather upper, accented with a signature Swoosh in off-white hairy suede. The latter material reappears on the toe box and back tab, marked with the Wings logo for an OG touch. Atop the suede tongue, a woven Nike Air tag displays the phrase ‘Give Them Flowers’ on the interior side. A multicolor floral print adds vibrant pops of color to the insole and translucent rubber outsole.

Name: Air Jordan 1 Low ALT PS 'Alternate Royal Toe'
Wmns Air Jordan 1 Elevate Low 'Hyper Royal Black'
Jordan Stay Loyal 3 'Black Cement'
Jordan Luka 2 Black Bright Crimson
Jordan 1 Mid Black Royal Blue
Jordan 1 Low Alternate Royal Toe
Jordan 4 Retro Red Cement
Description: The Air Jordan 4 Retro ‘Red Cement’ showcases color blocking that recalls the OG ‘White Cement’ colorway. The mid-top carries a white leather upper with tonal quarter panel netting and contrasting black accents on the molded eyelets and interior lining. Vibrant hits of Fire Red — accompanied by black speckled detailing — land on the shoe’s support wings, polyurethane midsole and heel tab. The latter features embossed Jumpman branding. A second Jumpman icon decorates the Flight tongue tag. Underfoot, a herringbone-traction rubber outsole delivers superior grip.

Name: Jordan 1 Retro High OG Palomino
Description: The Air Jordan 1 Retro High OG ‘Palomino’ merges a luxe build with OG-inspired two-tone color blocking. The sneaker icon carries a black leather upper, accented with aged brown nubuck on the toe box, Swoosh, heel overlay and collar flap. The latter is marked with a black Wings logo on the lateral side, while the woven tongue tag displays a Nike logo with metallic gold lettering. A contrasting off-white finish is applied to the midsole, built with stitched sidewall construction and encapsulated Air-sole cushioning. Underfoot, a brown rubber outsole features a traction pattern designed to grip the hardwood.

Name: Jordan 13 Retro Wolf Grey (2023) (TD)
Description: Built for a new generation of Michael Jordan fans, the Air Jordan 13 Retro TD ‘White Wolf Grey’ delivers a neutral colorway in celebration of the classic silhouette’s 25th anniversary. Dimpled overlays in white tumbled leather dominate the upper, featuring grey suede paneling and a forefoot built with white tumbled leather. An embroidered Jumpman in True Red adorns the tongue, while the 13’s signature holographic eye is embedded in the lateral collar. Underfoot, the outsole leverages herringbone traction pods for reliable grip.

Name: Jordan 1 Retro Low OG Black Toe (2023) (GS)
Description: Scaled down for big kids, the Air Jordan 1 Retro Low OG GS ‘Black Toe’ brings back an original 1985 colorway. The low-top carries an all-leather upper that combines a white base with contrasting black accents on the forefoot overlay, eyestay and signature Swoosh. Bold hits of Varsity Red settle on the heel and back tab, the latter marked with a stitched Wings logo. Nike Air branding decorates the tongue tag and sockliner. Encapsulated Air-sole cushioning enhances the midsole, rendered in a classic white finish and supported by a durable crimson rubber outsole.

Name: Jordan 5 Retro Low Dongdan
Description: The Air Jordan 5 Retro Low ‘Dongdan’ pays homage to the legendary streetball courts of Beijing. The low-top sports a black nubuck upper with contrast pink stitching and translucent netting on the quarter panel. A Jumpman icon adorns the silver reflective tongue, while the Dongdan tournament’s logo is embroidered on the back heel. The sneaker rests on a black polyurethane midsole, fitted with visible Air-cushioning and accented with pink shark-tooth detailing covered in black speckles. A pink-tinted translucent rubber outsole delivers grippy traction underfoot.

Name: Jordan 1 Retro High OG UNC Toe (PS)
Description: Inspired by Michael Jordan’s alma mater, the Air Jordan 1 Retro High OG PS ‘UNC Toe’ delivers a scaled-down model built for little kids. The high-top makes use of an all-leather upper, featuring a white quarter panel with contrasting black hits on the forefoot overlay, high-cut collar and signature Swoosh. University Blue accents make their way to the toe box, ankle and heel. The sneaker is mounted on a sturdy rubber cupsole that pairs white sidewalls with a Tar Heel blue rubber outsole.

Name: Jordan 1 Retro High OG Spider-Man Across the Spider-Verse
Description: The Marvel x Air Jordan 1 Retro High OG ‘Next Chapter' delivers a collaborative colorway tied to the animated film 'Spider-Man: Across the Spider-Verse.’ A play on the original ‘Chicago’ colorway, this reimagined take on the sneaker icon features a white leather upper with black patent leather on the collar and Swoosh. Scarlet overlays are composed of a patchwork mix of different textures and prints — a pieced-together design that nods to the multidimensional Spiderman universe. A retro Wings logo is stamped on the lateral collar flap, while a woven Nike tag decorates the nylon tongue. The high-top rides on a rubber cupsole that pairs aged sidewalls with a crimson semi-translucent rubber outsole.

Name: Jordan 4 Retro Thunder (2023) (GS)
Description: Made for big kids, the 2023 edition of the Air Jordan 4 Retro GS ‘Thunder’ brings back the coveted two-tone colorway originally released in 2006. The mid-top features a black nubuck upper with contrasting yellow accents. They land on the shoe’s molded eyelets, quarter panel and lower tongue, with the latter two components covered in black netting that reflect the AJ4’s original ’89 specs. Traditional Jumpman branding decorates the molded back tab and woven tongue tag. The sneaker rests on a yellow polyurethane midsole, enhanced with visible Air-sole cushioning and supported by a herringbone-traction rubber outsole.

Name: Jordan 4 Retro Thunder (2023)
Description: The 2023 edition of the Air Jordan 4 Retro ‘Thunder’ brings back the coveted colorway originally released in 2006 (and previously reissued in 2012). The upper is draped in smooth black nubuck, contrasted by hits of yellow on the molded eyelets, quarter panel, and lower tongue, with the latter two components covered in black netting. Jumpman branding appears on the Flight tongue tag and molded heel tab. Lightweight cushioning comes courtesy of a yellow polyurethane midsole, enhanced with an exposed Air-sole unit in the heel.

Name: Jordan 2 Retro Cement Grey
Description: The Air Jordan 2 Retro ‘White Cement’ treats Michael Jordan’s sophomore signature shoe to a simple makeover. The white leather upper features a tonal lizard-textured overlay, framed in black and grey piping and accented with a grey molded heel tab. The latter is marked with an embossed Nike wordmark, while a grey Wings logo adorns the tongue. A polyurethane midsole packs encapsulated Air-sole cushioning for a smooth ride. Inside the shoe, the sockliner displays a skyline graphic and the phrase ‘Look, Up in the Air.’

Name: Jordan 3 Retro Wizards
Description: The Air Jordan 3 Retro ‘Washington Wizards’ showcases a familiar design based on a PE colorway that Michael Jordan wore during his time in D.C. Featuring color blocking reminiscent of the OG ‘True Blue’ edition from 1988, the classic silhouette makes use of a white tumbled leather upper with grey elephant-print overlays at the toe and heel. Contrasting blue accents appear on the interior lining, molded eyelets, and the raised Jumpman logo that decorates the heel tab. A second Jumpman graces the tongue in copper-colored embroidery, matching the circular eyelets that dot the forefoot. The mid-top is mounted on a two-tone polyurethane midsole, equipped with a visible Air-sole heel unit and supported by a durable grey rubber outsole.

Name: Jordan 13 Retro Black Flint
Description: The Air Jordan 13 Retro ‘Black Flint’ dresses the legacy model in OG-inspired color blocking reminiscent of the ‘Flint’ colorway from 1998. Black mesh overlays dominate the upper, featuring a white leather toe box with synthetic grey suede along the midfoot and collar. A crimson Jumpman decorates the white leather tongue, while the 13’s holographic ‘cat eye’ graces the lateral ankle. Anchoring the sneaker is a panther paw outsole, fitted with white herringbone traction pods and an exposed carbon fiber shank plate.

Name: Jordan 1 Retro High OG Washed Pink (Women's)
Description: The Women’s Air Jordan 1 Retro High OG ‘Washed Pink’ delivers a pastel colorway of the foundational silhouette. The high-top dons a white leather upper with soft suede overlays in a muted pink hue. An aged pre-yellowed finish is applied to the midsole and breathable nylon tongue, the latter accented with a woven Nike tag. Additional branding elements include a pink suede Swoosh and an off-white Wings logo stamped on the lateral ankle. Underfoot, a pink rubber outsole features a traction pattern originally designed for pivoting on the hardwood.

Name: Jordan 1 Retro High OG Lucky Green
Description: The Air Jordan 1 Retro High OG ‘Lucky Green’ dresses the iconic silhouette in familiar color blocking that mirrors one-half of the 2009 Air Jordan 1 ‘Defining Moments Pack,’ inspired by Michael Jordan’s 63-point playoff performance against the Boston Celtics in 1986. The high-top sports a smooth leather upper, featuring a white base with contrasting hits of black on the forefoot overlay, Swoosh, and padded collar. Lush green accents land on the heel overlay and ankle flap, marked with a retro Wings logo on the lateral side. The shoe earns its OG designation with a woven Nike tag atop the breathable nylon tongue.

Name: Jordan 11 Retro Low Cement Grey
Description: The Air Jordan 11 Retro Low ‘Cement Grey’ showcases classic two-tone color blocking modeled after the inaugural spate of low-top releases from 2001. The upper combines white ballistic mesh with tonal webbing eyelets and a patent leather mudguard in a light grey finish. A miniature Jumpman in University Blue adorns the tongue and back heel. Underpinning the sneaker is a cushy Phylon midsole, supported by a translucent rubber outsole with grey herringbone traction pods and an exposed carbon fiber shank plate.

Name: Jordan 5 Retro UNC University Blue
Description: The Air Jordan 5 Retro SE ‘UNC’ showcases a familiar pastel hue inspired by Michael Jordan’s alma mater. The upper is crafted from University Blue nubuck with tonal TPU eyelets, ventilated quarter-panel netting and a woven jock tag at the heel. An embroidered Jumpman decorates the tongue, rendered in a reflective silver finish for added visibility in low-light conditions. Lightweight cushioning comes courtesy of a black polyurethane midsole, accented with speckled shark-tooth detailing and fitted with a visible Air-sole unit in the heel. Underfoot, a translucent herringbone-traction outsole provides optimal grip.

Name: Jordan 1 Mid SE Ice Blue (2023)
Description: The Air Jordan 1 Mid SE ‘White Ice Blue’ pairs the shoe’s timeless lines with a chilly color palette. The all-leather upper merges a crisp white base with pastel blue accents on the toe box, heel and collar flap. Contrasting hits of navy land on the signature Swoosh, collar and tongue, marked with an embroidered Jumpman logo. The mid-top rides on a durable rubber cupsole, featuring an Air-sole heel unit encapsulated within a lightweight polyurethane wedge.

Name: Jordan 1 Retro Low OG Doernbecher (2023)
Description: Designed by Riddhi Mahajan, the Air Jordan 1 Retro Low OG represents one of six footwear styles that make up Nike’s Doernbecher Freestyle XVIII collection. The classic low-top showcases vibrant hues that reflect Riddhi’s sunny worldview. Denoting the colors of a sunrise, ombre laces secure the leather upper, featuring lush green overlays, white quarter panels, and a violet Swoosh. ‘Radiate Positivity’ is printed across the lateral midfoot, while ‘Brand New Day’ is inscribed on the fluorescent green toe box. Underfoot, a translucent purple rubber outsole reveals Riddhi’s name and a daisy graphic.

Name: Jordan 13 Retro Playoffs (2023)
Description: The Air Jordan 13 Retro 'Playoff' 2023 brings back an original colorway first seen when Michael Jordan debuted it at the 1998 All-Star Game in New York City. The black quilted leather and suede upper features a hologram on the back heel, along with a Jumpman logo in a yellow circle on the tongue. Panther inspirations from MJ's black cat nickname make up the white midsole pods as well as the segmented outsole.

Name: Jordan 1 Retro High OG Reverse Laney (Women's)
Description: The Women’s Air Jordan 1 Retro High OG ‘Reverse Laney’ delivers a color-flipped version of an AJ1 High from 2013, featuring a two-tone palette inspired by Michael Jordan’s high school in Wilmington, North Carolina (and originally introduced via an Air Jordan 5 Retro+ from 2000). The familiar hues are deployed on an all-leather upper, highlighted by a Varsity Maize base with contrasting overlays in Game Royal. A black Wings logo is stamped on the lateral collar, while a black woven tongue tag displays crimson Nike Air branding. The high-top rides on a crisp white midsole, enhanced with encapsulated Air-sole cushioning and supported by a royal blue rubber outsole.

Name: Jordan 4 Retro SE Craft Photon Dust (GS)
Description: Made for big kids, the Air Jordan 4 Retro SE GS ‘Craft’ brings neutral tones and an elevated build to Tinker Hatfield’s original 1989 design. A subtle pale grey finish is executed on the leather upper, bolstered with a forefoot overlay in color-matched shaggy suede. Contrasting Pale Vanilla accents settle on the shoe’s molded eyelets, as well as Jumpman branding hits on the tongue tag and heel tab. In lieu of traditional netting, suede quarter panels are embellished with grid-embossed detailing. An exposed Air-sole unit enhances the white foam midsole, supported underfoot by a two-tone herringbone-traction rubber outsole.
Colorway: Photon Dust/Pale Vanilla/Off White/Grey Fog/Flat Pewter/Sail

Name: Jordan 5 Retro Aqua
Description: The Air Jordan 5 Retro ‘Aqua’ showcases a distinctive color scheme that recalls an AJ5 PE made for Chris Paul during his time with the New Orleans Hornets. The legacy silhouette makes use of a black nubuck upper with translucent quarter-panel netting for improved breathability. A bright teal Jumpman decorates the back heel and silver reflective tongue. Anchoring the sneaker is a black polyurethane midsole, featuring speckled yellow shark-tooth detailing and visible Air-sole cushioning in the heel. Finished in a vibrant turquoise hue, a translucent rubber outsole yields durable traction.

Jordan 5 Retro DJ Khaled We The Best Crimson Bliss (GS)
Description: Made for big kids, the DJ Khaled x Air Jordan 5 Retro GS ‘Crimson Bliss’ is taken from the ‘We The Best’ collection, comprising vibrant colorways of the classic silhouette that was introduced to the world by Mars Blackmon. A radiant pink hue is executed on the leather upper, equipped with quarter panel netting, a slimmed-down collar, and a quilted blue liner for a luxurious touch. An embroidered Jumpman logo adorns a reflective silver tongue, while the heel overlay features mismatched Nike Air and ‘We The Best’ branding. Speckled shark-tooth detailing enlivens the off-white foam midsole, fitted with visible Air-sole cushioning and supported by a translucent rubber outsole.

Name: Jordan 6 Retro Chrome Metallic Silver
Description: The Air Jordan 6 Retro ‘Chrome’ showcases a familiar design previously seen on the ‘Chrome’ Air Jordan 6 Low from 2015. The upper is crafted from solid black nubuck with silver Jumpman branding on the lace guard. Standard AJ6 details remain intact, including a windowed tongue, lace locks, and a spoiler-like heel tag. The mid-top is mounted on a black polyurethane midsole, accented with metallic silver detailing and supported by a translucent rubber outsole.

Name: Jordan Luka 1 Racer Blue
Jordan 4 Retro A Ma Maniére Violet Ore
Description: The A Ma Maniére x Air Jordan 4 Retro ‘Violet Ore’ delivers an elevated take on the legacy silhouette. The Atlanta-based retailer dresses the mid-top in a muted purple nubuck upper, accented with tonal quarter panel netting and a decorative chrome rivet embedded in the lateral collar. Woven Flight tongue tags display mismatched Jumpman and A Ma Maniére branding, while molded black heel tabs feature a raised Nike Air logo. Inscribed across the interior side of each heel tab is the phrase ‘It’s not about the shoes … it’s about where you’re going.’ Quilted textile lines the collar and insole for a comfortable fit. The sneaker rides on a cream-colored polyurethane midsole with visible Air-sole cushioning in the heel.

Jordan 1 Retro Low OG Zion Williamson Voodoo
Description: The Zion Williamson x Air Jordan 1 Retro Low OG ‘Voodoo’ shares a New Orleans-inspired theme with a companion Zion 2 colorway from June 2022. Braided rope laces secure the upper, featuring beige suede quarter panels and a brown suede toe box. Burlap-like overlays feature raw edges and mismatched color blocking in light brown, Oil Green and Fossil. In addition to exposed deco stitching, unique accents include an inverted mini-Swoosh on the forefoot and an embroidered voodoo-doll graphic on the lateral heel. An upside-down Wings logo is stamped on the brown suede heel tab, which lifts up to reveal mismatched ‘Voodoo’ and ‘Zion’ graphics on the interior side.

Jordan 7 Retro  Trophy Room New Sheriff in Town
Description: The Trophy Room x Air Jordan 7 Retro ‘New Sheriff in Town’ celebrates the championship silhouette’s 30th anniversary with a collaboration inspired by the ’92 Barcelona Games. The patriotic design nods to the original ‘Olympic’ Air Jordan 7, while the shoe’s moniker echoes a playfully taunting one-liner that Michael Jordan leveled at Magic Johnson and Larry Bird after an infamous Dream Team scrimmage. The suede upper features a crimson base with ivory overlays, a navy neoprene tongue, and multicolor heel tabs that reference the Olympic rings. Gilded accents — highlighted by a molded Jumpman and mismatched heel badges that display the Trophy Room logo with MJ’s Olympic jersey number — symbolize the Dream Team’s gold medal run. Additional special features include His Airness’ signature etched on the lateral heel and ‘New Sheriff in Town’ embroidered on the interior tongue.

Name: Jordan 1 Elevate High Titanium (Women's)
Jordan 4 Retro Midnight Navy
Description: The Air Jordan 4 Retro ‘Midnight Navy’ dresses the legacy silhouette in the same color blocking used on the OG ‘Fire Red’ colorway. The upper is constructed from white leather with black support wings, a matching black heel tab with embossed Jumpman branding, and navy molded eyelets. A second Jumpman icon adorns the woven tongue tag in crimson. The sneaker rides on a two-tone polyurethane midsole, featuring encapsulated Air in the forefoot and a visible unit in the heel.

Jordan 3 Retro Fire Red (2022)
Description: The 2022 edition of the Air Jordan 3 Retro ‘Fire Red’ brings back an OG colorway of the first Air Jordan model designed by Tinker Hatfield. Originally released in 1988, the sneaker carries a white leather upper with dark grey elephant-print overlays at the forefoot and heel. Contrasting crimson accents settle on the perforated leather collar, molded eyelets, and polyurethane midsole, featuring a visible Air-sole unit nestled in the heel. Matching hits of Fire Red distinguish the sneaker’s branding elements, including a Jumpman logo embroidered on the tongue and ‘Nike Air’ embossed on the heel.

Name: Jordan 1 Mid Sneaker School Game Winner (GS)
Description: Built for big kids, the Air Jordan 1 Mid GS ‘Game Winner’ spotlights Michael Jordan’s standout achievement before he went pro. In a nod to the athlete’s alma mater, the mid-top carries a leather upper in white and University Blue. The translucent Jumpman tongue tag resembles a basketball backboard, while a netting-like overlay atop the tongue continues the playful hoops theme. The sneaker’s lateral side displays black and white graphics that depict MJ scoring the winning shot of the 1982 NCAA Championship, while his UNC coach Dean Smith looks on from the sidelines.

Jordan 3 Retro Desert Elephant
Description: The Air Jordan 3 Retro ‘Desert Elephant’ showcases materials and color blocking that stay true to the iconic silhouette’s original 1988 release. The upper is constructed from black tumbled leather with signature elephant-print overlays in a light tan finish. The neutral hue is repeated on the collar, eyestay, and tongue, the latter accented with a crimson Jumpman logo. Supporting the mid-top is a white polyurethane midsole with a visible Air-sole unit nestled under the heel.

Name: Jordan 1 Retro Low OG Black Dark Powder Blue
Description: The Air Jordan 1 Retro Low OG ‘UNC’ continues a tradition of classic Jordan models draped in colors that pay homage to Michael Jordan’s alma mater. This pair utilizes a leather upper that combines a white base with contrasting black accents on the forefoot overlay and signature Swoosh. The heel panel is finished in Dark Powder Blue, matching the rubber outsole and woven Nike Air tongue tag. A retro Wings logo on the heel tab maintains the shoe’s OG aesthetic.

Name: Jordan 1 Retro Low OG SP Travis Scott Reverse Mocha
Description: The Travis Scott x Air Jordan 1 Retro Low OG ‘Reverse Mocha’ delivers a twist on the original ‘Mocha’ AJ1 Low from 2019. The upper combines a brown suede base with ivory leather overlays and the Houston rapper’s signature reverse Swoosh on the lateral side, featuring oversized dimensions and a neutral cream finish. Contrasting scarlet accents distinguish a pair of woven Nike Air tongue tags, as well as mismatched Cactus Jack and retro Wings logos embroidered on each heel tab. A vintage off-white rubber midsole is bolstered with encapsulated Nike Air cushioning in the heel and a brown rubber outsole underfoot.

Name: Jordan 1 Low OG Bleached Coral
Description: The Air Jordan 1 Retro Low OG ‘Bleached Coral’ brings a pastel pop of color to the classic silhouette. The low-top dons a mixed-material upper, highlighted by a white leather quarter panel, black cracked leather on the forefoot overlay, and pink suede on the perforated toe box. Additional hits of pink suede land on the heel overlay and back tab, featuring a contrasting black Wings logo. The sneaker is mounted on a traditional rubber cupsole with a hidden Air-sole heel unit encapsulated in lightweight polyurethane.

Name: Jordan 36 Low Light Orewood Brown
Jordan 36 Low Luka Doncic PE

Jordan 1 Mid White University Gold (Women's)
Description: The women’s Air Jordan 1 Mid ‘University Gold’ presents a sunny colorway of the timeless silhouette. The mid-top makes use of an all-leather upper, highlighted by a stark white base with yellow accents on the collar, Swoosh, and forefoot and heel overlay. A Jumpman icon graces the woven tongue tag, while a retro Wings logo is stamped on the lateral ankle. The sneaker rides on a rubber cupsole, featuring encapsulated Air-sole cushioning in the heel and a grippy traction pattern underfoot.

Name: Jordan Zion 2 Voodoo
Jordan 36 Flight School
Jordan 6 Retro Red Oreo
Description: The Air Jordan 6 Retro ‘Red Oreo’ brings a simplistic two-tone palette to the classic silhouette that Michael Jordan wore when he clinched the first of his six NBA championships. The mid-top sports a white leather upper with perforated detailing and a tonal Jumpman logo embroidered on the back heel. Covered in white speckles, crimson accents appear on the molded pull tab and polyurethane midsole, featuring an exposed Air-sole unit in the heel and a translucent rubber outsole underfoot.

Jordan 3 Retro Neapolitan Dark Mocha (Women's)
Description: The women’s Air Jordan 3 Retro ‘Neapolitan’ enlivens the legacy silhouette with pastel pops of color. The mid-top carries a white tumbled leather upper with signature elephant-print overlays in Dark Mocha. Jumpman branding decorates the tongue and back heel in contrasting pink and brown hues. A vintage off-white finish is applied to the traditional polyurethane midsole, featuring visible Air-sole cushioning and a glossy splash of Atmosphere Pink at the heel.

Name: Jordan 11 Retro Low 72-10
Description: The Air Jordan 11 Retro Low ‘72-10’ brings back a celebratory design theme first featured on an Air Jordan 11 release from 2015. Like its predecessor, this pair nods to the Chicago Bulls’ legendary 1996-96 season, when Michael Jordan led the team to a record-breaking 72-10 record. Rendered in low-top form, the sneaker makes use of a black tumbled leather upper with a tonal patent leather mudguard. Crimson Jumpman branding delivers color-popped accents on the tongue and heel. Lightweight cushioning is provided by a white Phylon midsole, fitted with full-length Air-sole cushioning and supported by a translucent rubber midsole. The Jordan 11 Low '72-10' will release on May 14, 2022.

Name: Jordan Zion 1 SP Naruto Kyuubi
Jordan 1 Retro High OG SP Utility Stash
Jordan ADG 4 Golf White French Blue
Jordan ADG 4 Golf Black Cement
Jordan 1 Mid Light Curry Cardinal
Description: The Air Jordan 1 Mid ‘Light Curry Cardinal Red’ features warm hues on a classic silhouette inspired by the 1985 original. The leather upper combines a crisp white base with pastel beige overlays and bold scarlet accents on the signature Swoosh and mid-cut collar. A red Wings logo adorns the lateral ankle, while Jumpman branding makes its way to the tongue tag and sockliner. The sneaker sits on a rubber cupsole, highlighted by white sidewalls and a grippy black rubber outsole.

Name: Jordan 1 Mid Light Smoke Grey Anthracite
Description: The Air Jordan 1 Mid ‘Light Smoke Grey’ features an understated palette entirely devoid of color. The mid-top makes use of a smooth leather upper that combines a white base with light grey overlays at the forefoot and heel. Contrasting hits of black settle on the mid-cut collar and signature Swoosh, the latter accented with contrast white stitching. Additional branding hits take the form of a Jumpman icon on the woven tongue tag and a retro Wings logo on the lateral ankle. Anchoring the sneaker is a durable rubber cupsole with an Air-sole heel unit encapsulated in lightweight polyurethane.

Name: Jordan 1 Low Bulls
Description: The Air Jordan 1 Low ‘Reverse Black Toe’ delivers a flipped colorway of the iconic OG colorway from 1985. The Chicago-inspired design features a leather upper that combines a crisp white base with Gym Red accents on the forefoot overlay and signature Swoosh. Contrasting hits of black land on the low-cut collar and heel overlay, marked with retro Wings logo in crimson embroidery. Jumpman branding adorns the tongue and sockliner. The low-top is mounted on a durable rubber cupsole, fitted with an encapsulated Air-sole unit in the heel.

Name: Jordan Zion 1 Duke
Jordan 3 Retro Muslin
Description: The Air Jordan 3 Retro SE ‘Muslin’ updates Tinker Hatfield’s original 1988 design with a recrafted build. In lieu of traditional leather, the upper is constructed from Muslin canvas with forefoot and heel overlays in Cement Grey suede. University Red accents land on the sneaker’s lower eyelets, as well as Jumpman branding hits atop the tongue and molded heel panel. The sneaker rides on an off-white polyurethane midsole with visible Air-sole cushioning in the heel. Underfoot, a durable grey rubber outsole provides grippy traction.

Name: Jordan 4 Retro Blank Canvas (Women's)
Description: The Women’s Air Jordan 4 Retro ‘Blank Canvas’ presents an undyed design ready-made for customization. The layered upper is constructed from off-white canvas, featuring raw edges and tonal stitching. Molded eyelets and embroidered Jumpman branding at the tongue and heel maintain the shoe’s one-note finish. An ivory-hued polyurethane midsole packs a visible Air-sole unit in the heel for lightweight cushioning. Underfoot, the herringbone-traction rubber outsole is accented with multi-color paint splashes.

Name: Jordan 1 Low Game Royal Blue Void (Women's)
Description: The women’s Air Jordan 1 Low ‘Game Royal’ brings vibrant tones to a classic silhouette based on the original 1985 release. The leather upper features a Blue Void base with Game Royal overlays and a light grey Swoosh. Branding elements include a Jumpman icon on the tongue, an embroidered ‘23’ on the lace keeper, and a stitched Wings logo on the heel overlay. The low-top rides on a traditional rubber cupsole, highlighted by white sidewalls and a navy rubber outsole.

Name: Jordan 12 Retro Playoffs (2022)
Description: The 2022 edition of the Air Jordan 12 Retro ‘Playoff’ brings back the shoe that Michael Jordan wore during his 1997 championship run. The mid-top sports an essential two-tone color scheme, featuring radiating stitched lines on the black leather upper and lizard-textured overlays in a contrasting white finish. The sneaker’s molded eyelets shine in metallic silver, while color-popped crimson accents land on the Jumpman-embroidered tongue and webbing heel loop. Performance benefits include full-length Zoom Air cushioning, a carbon fiber shank plate, and a rubber outsole with herringbone traction pods under the forefoot and heel.

Name: Jordan Why Not Zer0.5 Childhood
Jordan 3 Retro Cardinal Red
Description: The Air Jordan 3 Retro ‘Cardinal Red’ showcases a distinctive palette influenced by an OG colorway of the Air Jordan 7. The sneaker’s titular hue appears on the collar lining, molded eyelets, and raised Jumpman branding at the heel, all of which are contrasted by a white tumbled leather upper. A second Jumpman icon adorns the tongue in orange embroidery, while the 3’s signature elephant print overlays reinforce the forefoot and heel. The mid-top is mounted on a two-tone polyurethane midsole with a visible Air-sole unit nestled under the heel.

Name: Jordan Why Not 0.5 HTG Honor the Gift
Jordan 1 Retro High OG Dark Marina Blue
Description: The Air Jordan 1 Retro High OG ‘Dark Marina Blue’ dresses the iconic silhouette in classic two-tone color blocking. The all-leather upper features a black base with contrasting dark blue overlays along the forefoot, heel, collar and eyestay. A matching blue Swoosh is accompanied by a Jordan Wings logo stamped in black on the lateral collar flap. Atop the nylon tongue, a woven Nike Air tag nods to the shoe’s retro cushioning technology: an Air-sole unit encapsulated in polyurethane nestled in the heel of the rubber cupsole.

Name: Jordan Zoom Separate Black Sky Grey Red
Jordan Zion 1 Planet Z
Jordan 1 Mid Diamond Shorts
Description: The Air Jordan 1 Mid SE ‘Diamond’ dresses the classic silhouette in a simple two-tone palette celebrating the 75th anniversary of the NBA. The mid-top carries an all-leather upper that combines a clean white base with contrasting black accents on the forefoot overlay, signature Swoosh, and mid-cut collar. The tongue tag displays classic Jumpman branding framed in a geometric shape that nods to the NBA’s diamond anniversary. A white rubber midsole features an encapsulated Air-sole unit in the heel and a milky white translucent rubber outsole underfoot.

Name: Jordan One Take 3 White Gym Red
Jordan 1 Mid SE Light Iron Ore (Women's)
Jordan Westbrook One Take Black Grey
Jordan 6 Retro Little Flex Atmosphere (PS)
Jordan 6 Retro Little Flex Atmosphere (TD)
Jordan 4 Retro Red Thunder
Description: The Air Jordan 4 Retro ‘Red Thunder’, also known as 'Crimson', features familiar color blocking that recalls the coveted ‘Thunder’ colorway, originally released in 2006 and subsequently reissued in 2012. The mid-top sports a black nubuck upper with contrasting pops of crimson in lieu of the older shoe’s Tour Yellow accents. They appear on the sneaker’s molded eyelets, interior tongue, quarter panel, throat and midsole, which packs visible Air-sole cushioning under the heel. Jumpman branding decorates the tongue tag and heel.

Name: Jordan 36 Year of the Tiger
Jordan 1 Low Alt Black Grey (PS)
Jordan Westbrook One Take Black Cat
Jordan 11 Retro Cool Grey (2021)
Description: The 2021 edition of the Air Jordan 11 Retro ‘Cool Grey’ brings back a colorway first released in 2001 and retroed again in 2010. Celebrating the 20th anniversary of the original launch, the mid-top build is faithful to the original, featuring a nubuck upper with tonal webbing lace loops and a shiny patent leather overlay, all rendered in tones of Medium and Cool Grey. A white Jumpman logo is embroidered on the lateral ankle, while a stylized ‘23’ decorates the heel notch. Lightweight cushioning is provided by a full-length Air-sole unit housed within a white Phylon midsole. Underfoot, a translucent outsole reveals a carbon fiber spring plate for enhanced on-court responsiveness.

Name: Jordan 1 Mid Linen
Description: The Air Jordan 1 Mid ‘College Grey’ applies a neutral two-tone palette to a classic silhouette inspired by Peter Moore’s original 1985 design. The all-leather upper features a clean white base with contrasting overlays in a refined tan hue. Jumpman branding decorates the sockliner and woven tongue tag, while a retro Wings graces the lateral collar flap. The mid-top rests on a sturdy rubber cupsole, which houses an Air-sole heel unit encapsulated in lightweight polyurethane.

Name: Jordan 2 Retro Low SP Off-White Black Blue
Description: With the release of the Off-White x Air Jordan 2 Retro Low SP ‘Black Varsity Royal’, a relatively unheralded silhouette gets the Virgil Abloh treatment. The low-top carries a black leather upper with a tonal lizard-textured overlay and contrasting royal blue accents. They land on the molded heel panel, midfoot piping and exposed-foam tongue, featuring the Jordan Wings logo for an OG touch. Michael Jordan’s signature is scrawled across the lateral side, while Abloh leaves his mark with a plastic zip tie, medial-side Helvetica text and ‘SHOELACES’ printed on the laces. Faux cracking on the midsole gives the shoe an aged, distressed aesthetic.

Name: Jordan 1 Low Black White Grey
Jordan 14 Retro Low Shocking Pink (Women's)
Description: The women’s Air Jordan 14 Retro Low ‘Shocking Pink’ gives the sleek silhouette an energetic makeover. A bold shade of fuchsia is applied to the shaggy suede upper, accented with a black Jumpman badge on the lateral side. Matching black hits make their way to the collar, tongue and Phylon midsole, featuring the 14’s toothy detailing in a bright red hue. Encapsulated Zoom Air units provide responsive cushioning in the forefoot and heel, while a carbon fiber shank plate offers improved midfoot stability. Underfoot, a translucent pink rubber outsole utilizes a herringbone traction pattern for optimal grip.

Name: Jordan 3 Retro Pine Green
Description: The Air Jordan 3 Retro ‘Pine Green’ combines OG-style color blocking with updated materials. Black textured nubuck replaces traditional leather construction on the upper, which is enlivened with verdant green accents on the molded eyelets, perforated leather collar, and embroidered Jumpman branding atop the tongue. Forefoot and heel overlays are rendered in the 3’s signature elephant print, while the molded heel tab displays a second Jumpman icon. The retro silhouette is mounted on a white polyurethane midsole with contrast green detailing and visible Air-sole cushioning under the heel.

MSCHF Gobstomper Off-Lemon Edition
MSCHF Big Red Boot
Description: The MSCHF Big Red Boot presents a cartoonishly proportioned high-top from the Brooklyn-based creative collective known for whimsical and provocative footwear. A straightforward crimson hue suffuses the bulky boot, constructed with a single-mold-shell design and a sturdy TPU rubber shell. The bulbous silhouette features a padded collar that reaches midcalf, and a flat EVA outsole marked with horizontal treads and debossed MSCHF branding.

Name: MSCHF Gobstomper Sour Edition
MSCHF Super Normal Friends and Family Deer Hunter
New Balance 1906R Brighton Grey
New Balance 991v2 MiUK Stone Island Black
Description: The Stone Island x New Balance 991v2 Made in England ‘Black’ features a stealthy palette inspired by industrial spaces that have been converted into venues and clubs. The upper combines black nubuck overlays with olive mesh construction that resembles latticed metal. A woven tongue patch displays Stone Island’s compass logo, while a reflective ‘N’ adorns the quarter panel. Additional reflective accents land on the vamp overlays, eyestay, and heel and foxing windows. Lightweight cushioning arrives via a full-length FuelCell midsole, fitted with an ENCAP heel and semi-translucent ABZORB SBS pods. Underfoot, a translucent rubber outsole reveals Stone Island’s oversized compass logo.

Name: New Balance 9060 The Whitaker Group Missing Pieces Silver Moss Green
Description: The Whitaker Group x New Balance 9060 ‘Silver Moss Green’ is taken from the ‘Missing Pieces Pack,’ featuring colorful designs inspired by the bright future envisioned by today’s younger generations. The upper is built with pale green nubuck with open-cell mesh underlays in Hazy Peach. The lifestyle runner rests on a dual-density ABZORB midsole, fitted with SBS cushioning and a translucent CR device embedded in the heel. A diamond-pattern rubber outsole, inspired by the New Balance 860, delivers lightweight traction underfoot.

Name: New Balance 9060 Magnet
New Balance 9060 Vintage Indigo
New Balance 9060 Mushroom
New Balance 2002R Protection Pack Dark Moss
New Balance 2002R Protection Pack Sandstone
New Balance 530 White Pink
New Balance 998 Ronnie Fieg & Frank Lloyd Wright Foundation Broadacre City Chutney
Description: Launching as part of the two-piece ‘Broadacre City’ pack, the Ronnie Fieg x Frank Lloyd Wright Foundation x New Balance 998 Made in USA ‘Chutney’ celebrates the 35th anniversary of the lifestyle running shoe. The collaborative design showcases rich earth tones inspired by Broadacre City, a futuristic city concept developed by renowned architect Frank Lloyd Wright. The upper combines a cream-hued mesh toe box with pigskin suede overlays in brick red and olive green. Mismatched white and pink ‘N’ logos adorn the quarter panel in shaggy tan suede, while the custom sockliner features Frank Lloyd Wright branding and a Broadacre City sketch. The sneaker rides on New Balance’s ENCAP midsole with ABZORB cushioning in the heel.

Name: DynaSoft Nitrel v5 Bungee Lace Little Kid 'Bright Lapis'
New Balance 550 White Rain Cloud (Women's)
Description: The New Balance Women’s 550 ‘Rain Cloud’ pairs the shoe’s throwback lines with a refined, neutral color scheme. The retro silhouette makes use of a white leather upper with light grey accents. They settle on the signature ‘N’ logo, TPU heel counter, and the leather overlay that reinforces the padded mesh collar. New Balance 550 branding appears on the woven tongue tag, while a Flying NB logo decorates the back heel. Reflecting the model’s ‘80s basketball roots, a durable rubber cupsole anchors the low, featuring an exposed foam wedge on the medial side.

Name: New Balance 860v2 Aime Leon Dore Red
Description: Launching as part of a collaborative three-piece pack, the Aimé Leon Dore x New Balance 860v2 ‘Red’ brings back a performance running shoe originally released in 2012. The upper combines airy cream-colored mesh with durable synthetic overlays in silver and tan. A crimson ‘N’ logo adorns the red mesh quarter panel, while the tongue is marked with Aimé Leon Dore branding. The sneaker sits atop New Balance’s N-ergy midsole, featuring ABZORB cushioning in the heel and a durable rubber outsole underfoot.

Name: New Balance 1906R Black Metallic Silver
New Balance 1906R Cordura Pocket Black
Air Max 1 '86 OG Golf 'Big Bubble - Royal'
Nike Dunk Low Diffused Taupe (Women's)
Nike Zoom Vomero 5 Sail Light Orewood Brown (Women's)
Nike Air Max Plus Light Photography Old Royal
Nike SB Dunk Low TIGHTBOOTH
Description: The TIGHTBOOTH x Nike Dunk Low SB presents the Japanese brand’s take on the classic silhouette. The low-top carries a black suede upper with textured white leather overlays at the forefoot and heel. On the lateral side, an orange TIGHTBOOTH tag is appended to the reflective black leather Swoosh. Dual logos adorn the stuffed tongue, while orange insoles display mismatched TIGHTBOOTH and Nike SB branding. The sneaker is mounted on a black rubber midsole, contrasted underfoot by a grippy white rubber outsole.

Name: Nike Air Max Plus 25th Anniversary
Marcus Rashford x Zoom Mercurial Superfly 9 Elite FG 'Better Believe It'
Wmns Juniper Trail 2 GORE-TEX 'Pale Ivory Black'
Nike Air Force 1 Low '07 Premium University of Oregon PE
Description: The Nike Air Force 1 ’07 Premium ‘University of Oregon’ PE features a white leather upper offset with reflective piping. Textured suede accents in a warm shade of green recall the grass of football fields. A “Ducks of a Feather” wordmark appears on the cork sockliner, with the “Oregon O” embroidered on the heel. The sneaker includes a hang tag featuring similar motifs in metallic gold. The midsole is rendered in Sail, lending the shoe a pre-aged aesthetic. Underfoot, a light grey rubber outsole utilizes the original pivot-point traction pattern. Produced in a limited run of 2,200 units in partnership with Division Street’s Ducks of a Feather, each pair is housed in a specially designed Go Ducks box. Proceeds benefit participating University of Oregon student-athletes.

Name: Nike SB Dunk High Sweet Tooth Candy Corn
Description: The Nike Dunk High SB ‘Sweet Tooth’ takes inspiration from candy corn, the perennial Halloween treat. The leather upper combines a white forefoot with a gradient blend of orange and yellow across the midfoot and heel. Teeth mark indentations are found on the toe box, while the Nike SB tongue tag features a cautionary message on the interior side that reminds wearers, ‘Do Not Take Candy From Strangers.’ Inside the shoe, custom insoles display an all-over print made up of the cone-shaped confection.

Name: Nike Air Max Plus Patta FC Barcelona Culers del Món
Description: The Patta x Nike Air Max Plus ‘Home Kit’ dresses the retro runner in the signature colors of FC Barcelona. Finished in a gradient blend of navy and magenta, the mesh upper features dual Swoosh branding and a black TPU cage inspired by palm trees swaying in the wind. In addition to the traditional Tn badge at the heel, branding elements include Patta Air tongue tags, FC Barcelona lace jewels, and ‘Culers del Mon’ inscribed on the sockliner. Lightweight cushioning is provided by a two-tone polyurethane midsole, equipped with a whale tail-inspired shank and visible Air-sole units in the forefoot and heel.

Name: Ja 1 'Day One - Soft Pink'
Colorway: Medium Soft Pink/Diffused Blue/Cobalt Bliss/Citron Tint

Name: Nike Dunk Low Smoke Grey Gum 3M Swoosh
Description: The Nike Dunk Low ‘Smoke Grey Gum’ features reflective threads woven into the laces, which secure a white leather upper with grey suede overlays at the forefoot and heel. A reflective grey leather Swoosh sweeps across the side panel. Additional branding elements include a woven Nike tongue tag and an embroidered Nike wordmark on the back tab. The sneaker rests on a crisp white midsole, supported underfoot by a grippy gum rubber outsole.
Colorway: White/Light Iron Ore/Gum Light Brown/Smoke Grey

Name: Nike SB Dunk Low Born X Raised One Block At A Time
Description: The Born x Raised x Nike Dunk Low SB ‘One Block at a Time’ brings a raft of unique details to the classic silhouette. The LA-based streetwear brand outfits the upper in textured white leather with ornate perforations on the toe box and contrasting nubuck overlays in Dodger blue. ‘One Block at a Time’ is inscribed across the toe of each shoe, while a decorative emblem in pink embroidery decorates the lateral heel. A holographic effect enlivens the Swoosh and back tab, marked with a lenticular Born SB logo. The sneaker sits atop a white rubber midsole, featuring embossed lettering that spells out ‘On the Turf’ across the heel. Underfoot, the semi-translucent blue rubber outsole reveals oversized Born SB branding.

Name: Nike Air Max 1 Familia
Description: The Nike Air Max 1 ‘Familia’ celebrates young Latina women with a colorful interpretation of the lifestyle running shoe. A pink Swoosh in textured textile adorns the upper, crafted from tan leather and outlined in red piping with yellow deco stitching. Outlined in green textile trim, the suede mudguard is rendered in a vibrant pink hue, matching the Nike Air logo stamped on the back heel. ‘Familia’ branding appears on the right tongue tag and sockliner. The sneaker rides on an off-white polyurethane midsole, fitted with visible Air-sole cushioning and supported by a multicolor rubber outsole.

Name: Nike Full Force Low White Black Pewter
Description: The Nike Full Force Low ‘White Black’ features neutral tones on a new lifestyle model that takes inspiration from the Air Force 3. White leather is utilized on the upper, accented with a black Swoosh and fortified with a grey leather overlay around the collar. A throwback Force logo is emblazoned on the black nylon tongue, while embroidered Nike branding adorns the back heel. The sneaker rests on sturdy cupsole tooling, highlighted by vintage off-white sidewalls and a black rubber outsole.

Name: Nike P-6000 Flat Pewter
Nike SB Dunk Low Albino & Preto
Description: The Albino & Preto x Nike Dunk Low SB ‘Jiu-Jitsu’ delivers the Brazilian jiu-jitsu brand’s refined take on the classic skate silhouette. The low-top sports a light tan textile upper, featuring pearl weave construction traditionally used on jiu-jitsu uniforms. A black Swoosh with contrast white stitching decorates the side panel, while Albino & Presto’s AP logo graces the back tab. Anchoring the sneaker is a durable cupsole that pairs crisp white sidewalls with a grippy black rubber outsole.

Name: Nike SB Dunk Low Orange Emerald Rise
Description: The Nike Dunk Low SB ‘Orange Emerald Rise’ showcases hairy suede on the upper, featuring a base color in Emerald Rise with contrasting orange overlays at the forefoot and heel. The signature Swoosh appears in aqua blue suede, matching the Nike logo hits that adorn the tongue tag and back tab. The insole packs a Zoom Air unit in the heel for impact protection. Underpinning the sneaker is a durable rubber cupsole in Lemon Chiffon.

Name: Wmns Shox TL 'White Silver' 2023
Description: The 2023 edition of the Nike Women’s Shox TL ‘White Silver’ features a textured white mesh upper fortified with tonal TPU overlays and accented with a molded Swoosh outlined in metallic silver embroidery. Nike Shox branding appears at the tongue and back heel in Max Orange, delivering unexpected pops of color. The silhouette’s unique cushioning system takes the form of a series of polyurethane pillars, supported underfoot by a durable rubber outsole.

Name: Nike Dunk Low Pink Corduroy (Women's)
Nike Air Max Plus Spider-Man
Nike Air Force 1 Low '07 LX Amber Brown Phantom
Description: The Nike Air Force 1 ‘07 ‘Amber Brown’ utilizes a rosy beige hue on the upper, built with a combination of breathable canvas and tumbled leather. In addition to an ivory-colored suede Swoosh, branding elements include a woven Nike tag atop the tongue and a Nike wordmark embroidered on the back tab. Anchoring the low-top is an off-white rubber cupsole, enhanced with an Air-sole unit encapsulated in a lightweight polyurethane wedge.

Name: Wmns Shox TL 'Black' 2023
Nike Ja 1 EYBL Melon Tint
Description: The Nike Ja 1 ‘EYBL’ celebrates Nike’s Elite Youth Basketball League with a colorful rendition of Ja Morant’s debut signature shoe. The upper blends open mesh construction in Melon Tint with tonal synthetic leather overlays and a wraparound TPU Swoosh in a bright purple hue. A multicolor pattern enlivens the heel, marked with an embroidered EYBL logo on the lateral side. The low-top rests on a two-tone Phylon midsole, featuring a Jade Ice finish throughout the forefoot and a solid black heel with speckled detailing. A forefoot Zoom Air unit provides on-court responsiveness.

Name: Nike Air Max 90 Ballistic Neutral Olive
Nike Calm Slide Geode Teal
Description: The Nike Calm Slide ‘Geode Teal’ brings a vivid finish to a versatile slip-on that marries minimalist style with superior comfort. Rendered in a rich teal hue, the seamless build is crafted from lightweight and quick-drying foam. Nike Swoosh branding decorates the upper and footbed, with the latter featuring a textured top layer designed to hold the foot securely in place. The raised midsole delivers a cushy ride, while the full-length rubber outsole provides durable traction poolside or on the street.

Name: Ja 1 'Fuel'
Description: The Nike Ja 1 ‘Ember Glow’ brings an energetic palette to Ja Morant’s inaugural signature shoe. A bright crimson hue floods the upper, crafted from open-cell mesh with stitched synthetic leather overlays throughout the forefoot. Contrasting hits of color arrive via a blue TPU Swoosh and mismatched lavender and aqua tongue tags, each emblazoned with Ja’s personal logo. Lightweight cushioning is provided by a white Phylon midsole, fitted with a forefoot Zoom Air unit and supported by a durable black rubber outsole.

END. x Mastermind Japan x Sk8-Hi 'Black'
Description: The END. x Mastermind Japan x Vans Sk8-Hi ‘Black’ is taken from a capsule collection that reimagines the classic silhouette with a rebellious punk-rock sensibility. Mastermind’s signature skull and crossbones graphic is plastered across a black canvas backdrop on the medial side, while the opposite side features black suede construction with zippered closure, an elongated black leather eyestay, and a white leather side stripe. Atop the tongue, a woven Vans tag is accessorized with metal hardware. Anchoring the sneaker is a deconstructed rubber midsole with misaligned paneling. Underfoot, a translucent rubber outsole reveals Vans’ signature checkerboard print.

Vans Skate Authentic Palace Jeremy the Duck Black
Description: The Palace x Vans Skate Authentic “Jeremy the Duck - Black” is one of three colorways of the low-top skate shoe designed by the London skate and streetwear brand and Vans. A Summer 2021 release, the “Jeremy the Duck” Skate Authentic marries two skate empires together for a long overdue collaboration. Palace’s cheeky “Jeremy the Duck” mascot fuels the design and appears on an all-over print graphic across the black canvas upper. A black-and-white checkerboard product tag appears on the lateral side of the forefoot and white contrast stitching outlines each panel. Dual “Palace” and “Vans” branding is printed on the lateral side of white rubber midsole. Co-branding can also be found on the red license plate on the back of the shoe. Release date: July 2, 2021

Vans Sk8-Hi MTE 2.0 DX Valerian White (Women's)
Description: The Vans Sk8-Hi MTE 2.0 DX “Valerian/True White” is a pair of rugged, water-resistant high-tops from the California-based footwear brand. Vans uses their popular Sk8-Hi model as the inspiration behind a special remaking for inclement weather. The aforementioned water-resistant upper features purple leather eyelets as well as a tonal forefoot and mid-panel. Tonal water-proof suede covers the collar and heel. Vans outfits the durable shoe with their classic white leather jazzy stripe and includes a small branding tag near the collar. The inner is lined with an extra layer of warm to keep things extra cozy on those particularly frigid winter days. Completing the design is a white rubber midsole with a gum traction bottom that assists in conquering snow, slush and anything else that is thrown its way.

adidas Yeezy Foam RNNR Ararat (2020/2022)
Description: Debuting at London Fashion Week in February 2020, the Yeezy Foam Runner ‘Ararat’ launched without warning the following June through Kanye West’s Yeezy Supply website. The molded slip-on is constructed from a unique foam compound that blends lightweight EVA with harvested algae. Sculpted lines and a neutral monochromatic finish promote a streamlined, futuristic aesthetic, while a series of oval cut-outs enable airflow for ventilated comfort.
